<div class="container">
	<div class="homepage-about"><h1>What We Do</h1>
		<div id="about">
      <p>By leveraging the power of social media, Ramblethru helps you find the best things to do at your destination. No more opening 40 browser tabs to look at cluttered, confusing travel sites.</p>
      <p>See something interesting about your destination? Save it to your notes list. You can also browse other people's notes for additional recommendations about your destination.</p>
      <p>Later, when you're out and about at your destination, you can refer to your notes from your mobile device. No more carrying around scraps of paper, or forgetting the name of that restaurant you had read a rave review about.</p>
      <p>Life's too short to not have adventures. Make the most of them with Ramblethru. <b>Adventure awaits.</b></p>
     </div>
	</div>
		<article>
		</article>

	<section class="homepage-about-discover">
		<div class="discover">
			<h2>Discover</h2>
				<article>
					<div id="discover-about">
            Explore recommendations from your peers about your destination.
          </div>
				</article>
			<div id="map"></div>
			<div id="clicked-state"></div>
		</div>
	</section>
	<section class="homepage-about-create">
		<div class="create">
			<h2>Create</h2>
				<article>
					<div id="create-about">Create a personalized itinerary around them.</div>
				</article>
				<div class="font-awesome">
					<i class="fa fa-foursquare fa-5x"></i>
					<i class="fa fa-instagram fa-5x"></i>
					<i class="fa fa-yelp fa-5x"></i>
					<i class="fa fa-reddit fa-5x"></i>
				</div>
		</div>
	</section>
	<section class="homepage-about-go">
		<div class="go">
			<h2>Go</h2>
				<article>
					<span class="animated bounceInUp">
            <div id="go-about animated">Something here.</div>
          </span>
				</article>
				<ul>
				<li><i class="fa fa-bus animated wobble"></i></li>
				<li><i class="fa fa-plane animated lightSpeedIn"></i></li>
				<li><i class="fa fa-car animated rollIn"></i></li>
				</ul>
		</div>
	</section>
</div>
